title: Grateful Dead Live at Oakland-Alameda County Coliseum on 1991-12-30
description: Touch Of Gray, Victim Or The Crime, Row Jimmy, Big River-> Maggie's Farm, Ramble On Rose, Just Like Tom Thumb's Blues, Bird Song-> Promised Land China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Samson & Delilah, Ship of Fools, Saint Of Circumstance-> Jam*-> Drums-> Jam-> The Last Time-> Stella Blue-> Turn On Your Love Light, E: The Weight

reviews.review_text: Mind Left Body Jam.... To bad there isnt a nice soundboard of this show, because it was overall a solid show.  Also, between Saint and Drums there is a short Mind Left Body Jam.
Need SBD Where is the SBD!  This is a terrible audience copy of this show.  It is not fair to rate a show that has no quality.

MLB  or Dear Prudence? 1st off where is a better source this one is awful.  They have to be out there.  Anyhoo, is that a dear prudence or a MLB Jam outta Circumstance?  Other that that the show was a blast, this whole spread was except for New Years which I thought smelled like poopy.
Good Show - Bad Quality Recording What a shame there isn't a better copy of this show. This one sounds like it was recorded from a bad location in the coliseum.

absolutely NOT bad recording w/eq This is NOT a bad recording. If eq is added, it is execellent. The performance is excellent, as well. Set 2 is rough around the edges but the whole show is very potent.
